title: Immaculate Conception Co-Cathedral
author: pikaman59
pages:
The Immaculate
Conception
Co-Cathedral was built
in 1927 in St. Kitts and
Nevis. it is a historical
landmark and is a
church to honor St.
Christopher, the
person who the island
name is based on
(The Kitts was a
nickname for the
island that became
officially recognized.)
